<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="107" pageId="2" pageNumber="105" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,1591,1942]" pageId="2" pageNumber="105">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1591,1617]" pageId="2" pageNumber="105">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Face along paraface in upper 1/3 covered with long whitish or black pile (
<figureCitation box="[1084,1149,1591,1617]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1959,1983]" captionTargetBox="[164,1411,205,1917]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[164,1424,181,1936]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. A, C, D male of Cheilosia candida sp. n. B, E male of Cheilosia paralobi. A, B head, lateral view, C head, dorsal view, D, E antennae, lateral view. Scale bar, 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4402962" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4402962/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="105">Figs 1</figureCitation>
A–B), long as pile around ocellar triangle; eyes usually pilose (in some species without pile: 
<taxonomicName authority="Vujic et Radenkovic" authorityName="Vujic et Radenkovic" authorityYear="2020" box="[878,1230,1627,1654]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="candida" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[878,999,1627,1654]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="105">C. candida</emphasis>
Vujić et Radenković
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1235,1297,1627,1653]" pageId="2" pageNumber="105">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1235,1297,1627,1653]" pageId="2" pageNumber="105" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[1309,1436,1627,1654]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Convocheila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paralobi">
<emphasis box="[1309,1436,1627,1654]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="105">C. paralobi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[198,337,1663,1690]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Convocheila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laticornis">
<emphasis box="[198,337,1663,1690]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="105">C. laticornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); face wide, with facial tubercle nose-like; frons convex; antennal pits separated; basoflagellomere rounded or ellipsoidal, dark-brown/black with reddish markings (except in some specimens of 
<taxonomicName box="[1224,1354,1699,1726]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Convocheila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paralobi">
<emphasis box="[1224,1354,1699,1726]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="105">C. paralobi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Convocheila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cumanica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="105">C. cumanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with entirely black basoflagellomere); pile on scutum and scutellum mixed pale-yellow and black (black pile at notopleural area, at wing bases and on posterior margin of scutellum); pile on metathoracic pleuron long, whitish, and wavy apically; all legs black, except light-brown apical parts of femora, basal 1/3 and apical end of tibiae and ventral surface of tarsi; pile on legs mixed pale-yellow and black; abdomen microtrichose, predominantly covered with long pale pile (except the posterior half of lateral margins of terga 3 and 4 with black pile in some males of 
<taxonomicName box="[183,325,1915,1942]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Convocheila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laticornis">
<emphasis box="[183,325,1915,1942]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="105">C. laticornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="(Becker))" baseAuthorityName="Becker" box="[383,618,1915,1942]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Convocheila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="105" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hypena">
<emphasis box="[383,499,1915,1942]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="105">C. hypena</emphasis>
(Becker))
</taxonomicName>
. Male genitalia: ventral lobus of gonostylus sickle-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[1297,1372,1915,1941]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1315,1339]" captionTargetBox="[157,1431,854,1284]" captionTargetId="figure-250@4.[151,1436,849,1291]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Gonostylus of male genitalia, lateral view. A Cheilosia latifacies, B Cheilosia hypena, C Cheilosia cumanica. govl—ventral lobus of gonostylus. Scale bar, 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4402964" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4402964/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="105">Figs 2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1386,1424,1915,1941]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1728,1752]" captionTargetBox="[155,1434,937,1700]" captionTargetId="figure-1497@6.[151,1436,931,1704]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Male genitalia of Cheilosia candida sp. n., lateral view. A male genitalia without surstylus B surstylus. ep—epandrium, hp—hypandrium, ce—cercus, godl—dorsal lobus of gonostylus, arrow pointed dorsal prolongation on godl, govl—ventral lobus of gonostylus. Scale bar, 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4402968" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4402968/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="105">4A</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4402962" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4402962" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4402962/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="106" startId="3.[151,250,1959,1983]" targetBox="[164,1411,205,1917]" targetPageId="3">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1959,2020]" pageId="3" pageNumber="106">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,361,1959,1984]" pageId="3" pageNumber="106">FIGURE 1. A, C, D</emphasis>
male of 
<taxonomicName authority="Radenković &amp; Likov &amp; Ståhls &amp; Rojo &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Smit &amp; Petanidou &amp; Steenis &amp; Vujić, 2020" authorityName="Radenković &amp; Likov &amp; Ståhls &amp; Rojo &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Smit &amp; Petanidou &amp; Steenis &amp; Vujić" authorityYear="2020" box="[451,636,1960,1984]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="candida" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[451,636,1960,1984]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="106">Cheilosia candida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[642,753,1960,1984]" pageId="3" pageNumber="106">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[642,700,1960,1984]" pageId="3" pageNumber="106" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
B, E
</emphasis>
male of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Malski" authorityYear="1962" box="[843,1033,1960,1984]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="106" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paralobi">
<emphasis box="[843,1033,1960,1984]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="106">Cheilosia paralobi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A, B head, lateral view, C head, dorsal view, D, E antennae, lateral view. Scale bar, 1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,151,249]" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">
In the Mediterranean area, this subgenus comprises besides the four previously mentioned species in 
<bibRefCitation author="Barkalov, A. V." pageId="4" pageNumber="107" pagination="518 - 531" refId="ref12853" refString="Barkalov, A. V. (2002) Subgeneric classification of the genus Cheilosia Meigen, 1822 (Diptera, Syrphidae). Entomological Review, 82, 518 - 531." type="journal article" year="2002">Barkalov (2002)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Malski" authorityYear="1962" box="[242,373,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paralobi">
<emphasis box="[242,373,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">C. paralobi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[390,534,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Convocheila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cumanica">
<emphasis box="[390,534,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">C. cumanica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[550,694,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Convocheila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sulcifrons">
<emphasis box="[550,694,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">C. sulcifrons</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[753,895,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Convocheila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="laticornis">
<emphasis box="[753,895,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">C. laticornis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, also two additional species: 
<taxonomicName box="[1236,1352,187,213]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Convocheila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hypena">
<emphasis box="[1236,1352,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">C. hypena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Radenković &amp; Likov &amp; Ståhls &amp; Rojo &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Smit &amp; Petanidou &amp; Steenis &amp; Vujić, 2020" authorityName="Radenković &amp; Likov &amp; Ståhls &amp; Rojo &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Smit &amp; Petanidou &amp; Steenis &amp; Vujić" authorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Cheilosia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="107" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="candida" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">C. candida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[248,312,223,249]" pageId="4" pageNumber="107">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[248,312,223,249]" pageId="4" pageNumber="107" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
